procedure.name: PROC_FOR_LOOP
procedure.sql: BEGIN DECLARE i_1 INT DEFAULT 1; WHILE i_1 <= 5 DO SELECT CONCAT_WS ('', 'i=', i); SET i_1 := i_1 + 1; END WHILE; END;

procedure.name: PROC_FOR_LOOP1
procedure.sql: BEGIN DECLARE i_4 INT DEFAULT 1; DECLARE i_3 INT DEFAULT 1; DECLARE i_2 INT DEFAULT 1; DECLARE j NUMERIC; WHILE i_2 <= 5 DO SET j := i; SET i_2 := i_2 + 1; END WHILE; WHILE i_3 <= 5 DO SET j := i; SET i_3 := i_3 + 1; END WHILE; WHILE i_4 <= 5 DO SET j := i; SET i_4 := i_4 + 1; END WHILE; END;

procedure.name: PROC_FOR_LOOP_REVERSE
procedure.sql: BEGIN DECLARE i_5 INT DEFAULT 5; WHILE i_5 >= 1 DO SELECT CONCAT_WS ('', 'i=', i); SET i_5 := i_5 - 1; END WHILE; END;

procedure.name: PROC_FOR_LOOP_REVERSE1
procedure.sql: BEGIN DECLARE i_6 INT DEFAULT 5; DECLARE j NUMERIC; WHILE i_6 >= 1 DO SET j := i; SET i_6 := i_6 - 1; END WHILE; END;
